The bet365 Stadium is an all-seater football stadium in Stoke-on-Trent, Staffordshire, England and the home of Premier League club Stoke City. It has a capacity of 30,089 following the completion of expansion works in 2017.  Former player Sir Stanley Matthews' ashes were buried beneath the centre circle of the pitch following his death in February 2000. The stadium hosted the 2002 03, 2003 04 and 2004 05 playoff finals for the Conference National and on 16 April 2002, it hosted Englands under 21s international friendly against Portugals under 21s.
